<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 6:55PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Floyd,
south central Gordon and Bartow Counties through 730 PM EDT...
At 654 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Cartersville, moving
southwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail, heavy rain, and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Cartersville, Adairsville, Euharlee, Emerson, White, Kingston,
Plainville, Taylorsville, Cassville, Shannon, Pinson, Red Top
Mountain State Park, Folsom and Stilesboro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
